        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect front linings to confirm lining number R301 (Figure 1) or MA210 (Figure 2) has
                    been installed on both left and right side.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Either lining MA210 or R301 is correct if the same number is on both sides. They should
                    not be mixed on the same axle. If both wheels have the same number lining, the vehicle needs no
                    further repair. If lining is mixed, proceed to Step 3.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691101" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Brake Lining R301 is identified on the lining edge. Needs to be replaced if
                    mismatched.
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0691102" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Brake lining MA210 is identified on the lining edge and needs to be replaced if
                    mismatched.
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If it is determined that one side has lining number R301 (Figure 1), and the other side
                    has MA210, both sides must have new lining number MA210 installed (Figure 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Outboard Brake Drums</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving. When
                        working under a raised vehicle, support the vehicle with safety stands. Do not work under a
                        vehicle supported only by jacks. Jacks can slip and fall over.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Chock rear wheels.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Raise front wheels off the floor and put jack stands under front axle.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove wheels from hubs and slide brake drums off hubs. Replace mismatched brake shoes with
                        new Meritor shoe Kit Number KSMA2104720QP.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Slide brake drums over the new brake shoes and install and torque wheel lug nuts to proper
                        spec.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove jack stands and lower vehicle back to the floor.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Inboard Brake Drums</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving. When
                        working under a vehicle, support the vehicle with safety stands. Do not work under a vehicle
                        supported only by jacks. Jacks can slip and fall over.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Chock rear wheels.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Raise front wheels off the floor and put jack stands under front axle.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove hubcap and spindle nut. Slide wheel, hub and brake drum off of brake shoes.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Replace mismatched brake shoes with new Meritor shoe Kit Number KSMA2104720QP.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Slide wheel, hub and brake drum over the new brake shoes. Install outer wheel bearing and
                        spindle nut. Torque to correct spec and install nut lock and hubcap. If hub is oil filled, make
                        sure it is filled to the proper level with the correct lubricant.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove jack stands and let vehicle down to the floor.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcproc>
